-- Hungary April Retail Sales Drop Most Since 2010 on Electronics
-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 2012-06-25T07:00:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/hungary-april-retail-sales-drop-most-since-2010-on-electronics.html
Hungarian  retail sales  dropped the
most since 2010 in April as purchases of electronic goods and
furniture slumped.  Retail sales fell 2.7 percent from a year ago, the biggest
decline since June 2010, after a 0.9 percent increase in March,
the  statistics office  in Budapest said today in an e-mailed
report. The median estimate of 13 economists in a Bloomberg
survey was for a fall of 0.1 percent.  Sales of furniture and electronic goods slumped 2.4 percent
in April after rising 2.4 percent in March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
